social_posts.post_text: For the first time in almost 12 months, my newest collection of classes, The Rising, is now available. It took a lot of courage to get back in front of the camera, and in true Goldie fashion, poured my heart out, too. It’s the only way I know how to live. No walls. No secrets. No ulterior motives. Just the full spectrum of human emotion. I’m lucky to be able to feel to the capacity I do. It’s my superpower. Thank you for supporting me. I feel the love and it’s received and held closely.

The phrases I’m speaking in this video belong to the brilliant @zannakeithley. They live in my mind daily, and on my refrigerator. I speak them to friends & family. I read them to the women in my Women’s Betrayal Groups. I embody them. It’s important they live on my feed here so we can continue to remind ourselves that nothing in our lives, no matter how messy, abhorrent, or heartbreaking they are, is a mistake on us. Behavior will always speak louder than words. Though, words like these heal. 

Background info on this video: this is the teaser I made for my newest collection of yoga classes called, The Rising. Classes can be found on my website/link in bio. For those of you who have already purchased & gifted, your support these days means more than ever before. I see you, I feel the community, and I thank you SO, so much. #goldieyoga #poetry #heartbreak #affairrecovery

I love this little, big boy so much that it physically hurts to try and describe it. Do you know what I mean?! Ugh. Drop me your one liner of how you describe the love you have for your child.  #lumicobra #love

This photo shows a static moment in time, which is why social media is so deceiving. It's me and the babes on NYE 2022. I've been told the first holidays alone are the worst, but once they're behind you, you never have to do "the first" again. I'm not sure I'm buyin' it. I'll lyk next year.

I spent the last couple of weeks offline in FL, with my kids and family. I barely kept my head above water. My heart hurt everyday. When I see this photo (and many others like it) all I see is a missing puzzle piece. I fear that feeling won't ever subside. I'll continue to keep it real here. I always have, because that's the only way I know how.

Ugh man, I unconditionally loved that man for better or for worse. Didn't matter. I was in it for the long haul because life gets messy and I was ok with all of the seasons and chapters, and gosh darn-it if your kids don't make you want to be the best version of yourself then what will?

One-liners on IG don't work for me right now. If you're still reading and here with me, thank you. I know I'm not alone...I also know it doesn't matter how many people are in your support court. The only way to move forward and heal is to feel. All of it. My hope for 2023 is peace and stability. To have more daily grace and not just grit.

The convenient path is rarely, if ever, the right path. Fast fixes are bullshit (and for the weak) and numbing is why people hurt others in the first place. Remember, hurt people hurt people. Instead, do the work, deep introspection and self honesty - that’s what will help us move forward in our grief. Not time. Don’t wait for the clock hands to do the work for you. It’ll never happen. And always, always remember: “Don’t compare your insides to somebody else’s outsides.” (Thanks @glennondoyle for the punchy one liner.”

When the heart
Is cut or cracked or broken
Do not clutch it
Let the wound lie open
Let the wind
From the good old sea blow in
To bathe the wound with salt
And let it sting.
Let a stray dog lick it
Let a bird lean in the hole and sing
A simple song like a tiny bell
And let it ring
Let it go.
Let it out.
Let it all unravel.
Let it free and it can be
A path on which to travel.
-Michael Leunig

The kids and I in FL over Christmas. Not a moment passes, especially during times like this, that I don’t feel the sting of the missing link. The missing for my kids. The missing for myself. I just keep breathing and reciting to myself…In the words of @ewood02 “If not this, then something better.”

This is special. It deserves a square on my grid. It deserves realestate here because it will forever be a reminder to keep my growth front and center. To refrain from dedicating and pouring so much of myself and my life into a single human being. (Except my kids, of course. Those silly dillys are happily my number one.)

The grief I’m living with is so harsh. To be transparent- I really don’t know how I’m doing this. 

Just last night I was watching the kids eat at the kitchen island thinking;

 “What the fuck happened? How is this real?” 

I just stared at them. Billie Holiday in the background. A candle burning and the smell of chicken nuggets and blueberry waffles floating above my nose. 

I wish I hadn’t been getting love letters up until the end. I wish I hadn’t been blindsided. I wish I had known this is where it was headed. Maybe it wouldn’t feel so jarring. 

Now that I’m the only one standing in my way, I’ve made more room for creative expression. I’ve heard so many times “I don’t know how you’re doing it” and actually, just writing this is helping me realize that I have five practices getting me through each day. 
1. My genuine adoration for the role of motherhood
2. Creative arts like writing and pottery
3. Boxing
4. Weekly therapy
5. Incredibly deep sleep

One day, my dear Zuma Z, your heart will be broken and you’ll feel like you can’t go on. I’ll be there to remind you that those who are meant for you, don’t break you. They protect you. I am so incredibly proud of myself for being able to walk the walk. Being able to live in action, not hypocrisy. Being able to model for my children the advice I will one day have to pass on to them. Women are so F’n strong. Incredibly proud to be one and even prouder to be raising one. #motherhood #affairrecovery #minneapolis #minnesotalove

THE #1 thing I've learned over the last excruciating 11 months is not only how much I can withstand and bear, but just how healthy I am. My therapist often says "Gosh, Goldie. You are so fucking healthy. It's wild how you're facing all that you are and not numbing or running." Yeah. I am healthy. I am heartbroken, and I will be ok. I just can't see my future in detail like I used to be able to. Anyone else feel this way? I'd love to hear your thoughts if you feel like sharing them. Divorce sucks.

My cup runneth over. My Birthday has always been my favorite “holiday” and my family flew in to make sure this year (another first) felt no different. The both/and concept is one I’m real familiar with these days. I’m both full to the brim with gratitude for a family that ALWAYS SHOWS UP, and simultaneously melancholy. Last year on my birthday he took me to lunch, kissed me goodbye and jumped in an Uber (from the restaurant) to board a plane to see his affair partner. It’s hard to look forward when I’m still trying to make sense of the past. My birthday wish during both cakes this year? Peace. Just peace.

My proudest creations. These 2 humans I grew, birthed and will nurture until my last breath on earth is what life is all about! “Happy.” It’s what Zuma is running around saying today and I echo her. I’m happy you guys! I did the work and I am so, so incredibly happy to be where I am today. A blessing in disguise. Mother’s Day 2023 ❤️

What's happening to Goldie Yoga now that @golden_design_group_mn exists?

Right around the time Zuma was born, I started to feel a strong urge that it was time to evolve from teaching yoga, and step into using the various other skills I not only possess, but am passionate about putting to use. It's been 14 years working for myself as "Goldie Yoga" and it's been nothing short of marvelous. 

There was never a question of what I would do next, but rather, when would I take the leap and turn the page. I've always said if I wasn't teaching yoga, I'd work in the industry of interior design, space planning and construction. I know the exact moment I decided to execute. I was listening to a @melrobbins podcast about reimagining your future, and when the pod ended, I opened my laptop, became hyper-focused, wrote a business plan (with checkboxes next to each task & idea), called my family so that I could speak into existence my new plan (speaking your dreams into existence is real. Start talking about them.) and started going down the list executing what I needed to do to get from "there" to "here." 

My Class Bundles, Programs, Mentorships and Betrayal Group on GoldieYoga.com will live on and exist, dare I say, forever? I will continue to offer all of those things, but I will not be filming new classes or teaching any public classes.

To read more about who I am outside of yoga, where I come from and what credentials and experience I hold, head to my link in bio. The best way to support me right now is by spreading the good word of Golden Design Group, and of course, working with me! 

Keep evolving. 

LOVE.

📸 @nickjwang

It recently dawned on me that I've been given a "second chance." A second chance at creating a new life with SO. MUCH. WISDOM! A growth and maturity from having been married, having children, buying a home, getting divorced, getting older…and the list goes on. I don't regret a single moment of my “past life” and feel higher than a kite these days living out dreams and experiences I never imagined would be part of my story. You guys, it's EPIC! I'm taking FULL advantage of who I am, where I am, and ALL of the magic that's around me. I feel reborn in a way. Like, who is this girl?! The darkness and pain I endured was so worth feeling and processing, because if I could share with you some of the shit I'm doing these days, you wouldn't believe it. For those of you in the painful dark, trying to make sense of the shit life may be throwing at you, don’t try to make sense out of the illogical. Instead, FEEL the pit of pain and confusion and be IN IT so you can rise again. Without hitting the bottom, you’ll never reach the top. You gotta feel it to heal it.

It feels both ironic and fitting that this photo of my Zuma girl and her untamed hair live side by side next to my last post, ft. my untamed locks. As Zuma grows up, I’ll teach her the most important thing to remember as a woman; 1. Your gut rarely leads you astray. 2. Not sure if someone is healthy for you? Check in with your central nervous system. It doesn’t lie. The peace and calm I have in my day to day life is something I have not felt in sooooooo loooooong. It feels amazing to be on the other side of it all, you guys. I don’t think being “healed” is something I’ll ever fully be- as my specific story will always feel surreal. But, I do believe my best years and experiences haven’t happened yet. I also feel my biggest love and deepest friendships are in front of me. Oh, how I’ve earned these feelings. Hang in there if you’re behind me in the divorce process. I promise, it gets better than anything you could write yourself. Xo

My cup runneth way over. Spent the weekend in Grand Marais (first time there for me) and have to say, my nervous system was like whooooaaaaaa what’s relaxation?! I haven’t felt this unplugged in years. We put OOO messages on and hit the road jamming the whole way there. The only thing on the agenda was to have no agenda. No time keeping. No wake up alarms. Nada. What a beautiful, beautiful part of the country. Such New England vibes. Back to work and feels so good to be home and refreshed. #grandmarais #thompsoniteinn #lakesuperior
Second chances.

In a short couple of weeks he starts Kindergarten(!!?!) Just over a year ago my life was in complete turmoil. The rug ripped out from under me and every part of my life in an upheaval. From my marriage surprise ending, nursing an infant around the clock, my career change, not knowing where we were going to live, and most importantly, my heart so shattered I thought I was going to die from the pain. Literally. I’m here to tell all of you who are experiencing devastating times…times you don’t believe you’ll survive- you will and you can do this. Please, hang on. Break down AND get back up. Splash some water on your face and then repeat. Both are required to get to the other side. To see the light. To climb the trees and feel the breeze. Smiling, gut laughing, even loving again will happen. I promise. Do your work AND hit the cold bathroom floor mid sob. BOTH lead you to the light. My current affirmation I tell myself when I feel the feels: “It’s all just an experience.” No need to label, put it in a box, figure out the ending, or control the timeline. It’s. All. Just. An. Experience.

What a beautiful little day my kids and I were lucky enough to experience. Zuma tested Ryan today to see if it was real love and decided to take a bare-ass, massive 💩 on his SUP and he didn’t even flinch. Only hysterically laughed with me. HE cleaned it up with extra diapers and when I asked if there was blood in it( thought I saw red..she’s fine, no blood. Not to worry) -he full on re-opened the diaper and examined it. (I know!!!!!) Another parent standing by with two babies overheard me ask that gross question and he said to us “now that’s a parenting question if I’ve ever heard one.” Unreal. He’s so f’n solid.
There aren’t enough words for this sweet, gentle, and caring man, so I’ll let his kind eyes say it all. #secondchances

My Zuma baby is 2! Yesterday was such a pleasant day. As I reflected on the last 365, there’s such a stark contrast of where I was on 10/9/22, when I threw Z her first bday party surrounded by women only, versus this year, where the 4 of us could celebrate our sweet girl together. All things aside, this is life. This is now, and this is reality. I’m so incredibly proud of myself and all the work I’ve done to be able to do that with genuine, authentic kindness. I’ve come so far and I’m SO proud of my children. Never underestimate what you’re capable of. I surprise myself constantly with who I’ve become and who I am becoming.

We spent a handful of days in La Jolla (his first time there!) and boy it’s incredible how vacation completely resets your system. We stayed at my favorite hotel, slept in, ran every morning, lounged at the pool, ate at the best restaurants in town, saw fam and he met a bunch of my close friends. 

I showed Ryan where I used to live…where we brought Lumi home for the first time. Took him to my fave coffee shop where steel memories🔒still live. Ran some of my favorite coast runs and visited my old yoga studio. At times it was surreal and one of those “both/and” scenarios I’ve close to mastered. I could have never predicted showing another partner around La Jolla, and yet simultaneously, I was so incredibly grateful for the opportunity in those moments. 

Divorce sucks AND you can make your second chance be anything you want it to be.

I look sad because I am. I share this not because I want you to feel bad for me. I’m ok. I’m both sad and ok. Duality in divorce. It’s 4p the day before Thanksgiving and I’m sitting alone at a restaurant thinking about how hard these winter holidays will be for the next 16 years. I suppose when the kids are older they’ll choose who they want to spend them with? For now, I have to get into a new and unfortunate mindset about how it’s “just another day.” Hard to do for someone like me who grew up loving the holidays with my in-tact family traditions and the hype my parents created. I see so many of you mothers on here talking about how tough this time of year is and how hard you’re working to re-wire your brain/thinking. I can’t thank you enough for being so honest about these feelings. It really helps tremendously to read them and I feel less alone. So, I figured I’d pass it forward. I never imagined my life with two young kids, one a baby, being shuttled back and forth. All this to say, we’ve made it through hell and back…we will make it through this, too. Not because we want to, but because we have to.

and here you are living 
despite it all
-Rupi Kaur
